exports[`Article JSON-LD snapshots > /resources/research-peptides-uk 1`] = `
[
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@id": "https://phlabs.co.uk/resources/research-peptides-uk#article",
    "@type": "Article",
    "articleBody": "If you are sourcing research peptides in the UK in 2026, the calculation has changed. Post-Brexit customs delays, rising shipping temperatures, and tighter expectations from university ethics committees mean a US or EU supplier that worked in 2020 often no longer makes sense. British labs increasingly insist on a UK-based supplier with HPLC ≥99% purity, batch-specific CoAs, and next-day domestic dispatch . This guide covers what to insist on, which compounds drive the most active UK research, and how to browse the full PH Labs catalogue . Why Source Research Peptides from a UK Supplier Three practical reasons dominate: **1. Cold-chain integrity.** Peptides are temperature-sensitive. International shipments routinely sit in customs holding for 3–7 days at uncontrolled temperatures. A UK supplier dispatching by Royal Mail Tracked 24 or DPD next-day keeps the cold chain under 48 hours end-to-end. **2. Brexit customs friction.** EU and US imports now require commercial invoices, HS codes, and frequently VAT-on-import payment at delivery. A domestic UK order avoids all of this — what you pay at checkout is what you pay total. **3. CoA documentation in English, batch-matched to your vial.** UK suppliers serving British research labs default to batch-specific HPLC certificates with the chromatogram, retention time, and purity percentage clearly labelled. Many overseas suppliers still ship "generic" CoAs reused across batches, which fails most ethics-committee documentation standards. The Compounds British Labs Order Most Based on UK ordering patterns across 2025–2026, five compounds dominate domestic research peptide demand: Retatrutide UK: The Highest-Demand Frontier Compound Retatrutide is currently the single most-searched research peptide in the UK, driven by Phase 2 data showing −24.2% body weight reduction at 48 weeks (Rosenstock et al., 2023). Its triple receptor architecture — simultaneous GLP-1, GIP, and glucagon receptor activation — makes it a unique tool for dissecting metabolic pathway contributions. UK ordering volumes for retatrutide have grown roughly 4× year-on-year as British metabolic research groups expand triagonist work. BPC-157 UK: The Tissue-Repair Workhorse BPC-157 remains the most consistently ordered tissue-repair peptide in the UK. Its activity at the FAK-paxillin pathway, VEGFR2 upregulation, and prostaglandin-independent gastroprotection give British researchers a single reagent that crosses vascular, musculoskeletal, and epithelial research models. Read the full mechanism review: BPC-157 and Tissue Repair: The Preclinical Evidence . Tirzepatide and Semaglutide: The GLP-1 Reference Standards For UK metabolic research, Tirzepatide (dual GLP-1/GIP) and Semaglutide (GLP-1 mono-agonist) remain the comparator reference standards against which newer compounds are benchmarked. A direct mechanistic comparison is available in Retatrutide vs Tirzepatide vs Semaglutide . What a Real UK CoA Should Show A legitimate Certificate of Analysis from a UK supplier must include: • **Batch number** matching your vial label exactly • **HPLC chromatogram** (the graph showing peaks against retention time) • **Retention time** in minutes, with the target peak identified • **Purity percentage** (≥99% for research-grade, calculated from peak area integration) • **Mass spectrometry data** confirming identity (±1 Da of calculated mass) • **Analysis date** within the last 12 months • **Laboratory signature** or analyst initials If any of these are missing — particularly the chromatogram itself or a batch-matched analysis date — the document is not a real CoA. For a full walkthrough of how to read these documents, see How to Read an HPLC Certificate of Analysis . How to Vet a UK Peptide Supplier in Five Minutes Run this checklist before placing your first order with any UK supplier: **1. Can they email you a sample CoA before purchase?** A legitimate supplier will share a redacted historical CoA on request. If they refuse or only offer a "generic" certificate, do not buy. **2. Do they list a UK business address and contact phone?** A web form is not enough. UK-registered suppliers must publish a Companies House number and business address. **3. Is cold-pack shipping standard, not extra-cost?** Peptides must ship insulated. If cold-pack is an upsell or seasonal extra, the supplier is cutting corners. **4. Do they make any therapeutic or medical claims?** Research peptides are sold strictly for in-vitro and preclinical research. Any supplier marketing weight loss, muscle growth, or anti-ageing benefits to consumers is operating outside the research-chemical scope and likely cuts corners on analytical work too. **5. Do they respond to a technical question?** Email and ask about solubility, recommended reconstitution diluent, or expected retention time. A supplier serving real research labs will answer in a sentence; a reseller will not. Where to Buy Research Peptides UK PH Labs is a UK-based research peptide supplier dispatching from a domestic warehouse with next-day Royal Mail Tracked 24 and DPD options. Every order ships with a batch-specific HPLC ≥99% purity certificate, cold-pack insulation, and full technical documentation. Browse the full UK research peptide catalogue or jump directly to the most-ordered compounds: Retatrutide , Tirzepatide , Semaglutide , BPC-157 , TB-500 . For analytical background, see our Lab Reports archive and the Quality Control overview.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "PH Labs UK",
      "url": "https://phlabs.co.uk",
    },
    "datePublished": "2026-05-24",
    "description": "Research Peptides Uk: resource notes and references from PH Labs UK.",
    "headline": "Research Peptides UK: The 2026 Sourcing Guide for British Laboratories",
    "image": [
      "https://phlabs.co.uk/og-image.jpg",
    ],
    "inLanguage": "en-GB",
    "isAccessibleForFree": true,
    "mainEntityOfPage": {
      "@id": "https://phlabs.co.uk/resources/research-peptides-uk",
